# Atlas UI

Atlas UI is a React component library shipping 60+ primitives and composites.
It is consumed by every Atlas product (web, mobile-web, embedded SDK).

## Stack

- **React** 18.3 (peer dep; supports 18+)
- **TypeScript** 5.6 (strict, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`)
- **Tailwind CSS** 4 with design tokens from `tokens.ts`
- **Build tool:** Vite (library mode, ESM-only output)
- **Primitives:** Radix UI for behavior, shadcn conventions for styling
- **Testing:** Vitest + React Testing Library (unit), Playwright + axe (a11y)
- **Storybook** 8 with the a11y, essentials, and interactions addons
- **Chromatic** for visual regression

## Directory layout

```
src/
├── index.ts                 # Single barrel — all public exports
├── components/
│   ├── Button/
│   │   ├── Button.tsx
│   │   ├── Button.stories.tsx
│   │   ├── Button.test.tsx
│   │   └── index.ts         # Re-exports Button + ButtonProps
│   ├── Dialog/
│   └── …
├── hooks/
│   ├── useMediaQuery.ts
│   └── …
├── lib/
│   ├── cn.ts                # tailwind-merge + clsx wrapper
│   └── cva.ts               # class-variance-authority helpers
└── tokens.ts                # Design tokens exported for consumers
```

## Release model

- Semver. Breaking changes require a major bump and a migration note in CHANGELOG.md
- Published to npm as `@atlas/ui`
- Every change ships a story + test + (if visual) a Chromatic baseline

## What this library does NOT do

- No data fetching — components are presentational
- No application state — Atlas apps handle their own state
- No router dependencies — components work in any React app
- No CSS-in-JS runtime — Tailwind utilities only
